<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10639&amp;p=120279#p120279"><![CDATA[
If something in a page on the wiki is unclear, someone might try to help you by editing the page to make it more clear. I didn't see it as particularly aggressive.<br /><br />The &quot;delta counter&quot; is just the channel's current output level, 0-127. A 0 bit from the shift register means subtract 2; a 1 means add 2. But don't add or subtract if doing so would push the output level outside the range 0-127.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Nov 05, 2013 2:07 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
